# Aggregate total downtime (in minutes) by Production Location
agg_downtime <- data %>%
  group_by(PRODUCTION_LOCATION) %>%
  summarise(total_downtime = sum(ACTUAL_WORK_IN_MINUTES, na.rm = TRUE))

# Plot total downtime by Production Location
ggplot(agg_downtime, aes(x = PRODUCTION_LOCATION, y = total_downtime)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "lightblue", color = "black") +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Total Downtime by Production Location",
       x = "Production Location",
       y = "Total Downtime (in Minutes)")

# Boxplot for downtime by repair type
ggplot(data, aes(x = MAINTENANCE_ACTIVITY_TYPE, y = ACTUAL_WORK_IN_MINUTES, fill = MAINTENANCE_ACTIVITY_TYPE)) +  # Replace 'Repair_Type'
  geom_boxplot() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Downtime by Repair Type",
       x = "Repair Type",
       y = "Downtime (in Minutes)") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("skyblue", "lightcoral")) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 0, hjust = 0.5))

machine_downtime <- data %>%
  group_by(EQUIPMENT_ID) %>%
  summarise(downtime_count = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(downtime_count))

# Assuming 'equipment_info' contains EQUIPMENT_ID and EQUIPMENT_DESC columns
equipment_info <- data.frame(
  EQUIPMENT_ID = c(300025792, 300017655, 300115000, 300026891),  # Example
  EQUIPMENT_DESC = c('Conveyor Belt', 'Filling Machine', 'Labeler', 'Bottle Capper')  # Example descriptions
)

# Merging the two dataframes on EQUIPMENT_ID
merged_data <- left_join(machine_downtime, equipment_info, by = "EQUIPMENT_ID")
